                'description' => '<p><b>Mencius</b> (<span></span> <i title="English pronunciation respelling"><span>MEN</span>-shee-əs</i>) or <b>Mengzi</b> (372–289 BC or 385–303 or 302<span> </span>BC) was a Chinese philosopher who has often been  described as the "second Sage", that is after only Confucius himself.</p><p><span id="History"></span><span id="Biography"></span>
