                'description' => '<p><b>Shao Yong</b> (Chinese: <span lang="zh">邵雍</span>; pinyin: <i><span lang="zh-Latn-pinyin">Shào Yōng</span></i>; Wade–Giles: <i><span lang="zh-Latn-wadegile"><b>Shao Yung</b></span></i>; 1011–1077), courtesy name <b>Yaofu</b> (堯夫), named Shào Kāngjié (邵康節) after death, was a Song dynasty Chinese philosopher, cosmologist, poet and historian who greatly influenced the development of Neo-Confucianism in China.
