<p><b>Siddhasēna Divākara</b> (Jain Prakrit: <span lang="pka">सिद्दसेन दिवाकर</span>) was an <i>Digambara monk</i> in the fifth century CE who wrote works on Jain philosophy and epistemology. He was like the illuminating lamp of the Jain order and therefore came to be known as <i>Divākara</i> "Lamp-Maker". He is credited with the authorship of many books, most of which are not available. <i>Sanmatitarka</i> (‘The Logic of the True Doctrine’) is the first major Jain work on logic written in Sanskrit.</p>',
