        'description' => '<p><b>Sally J. Scholz</b> (born 1968) is an American Professor of Philosophy at Villanova University and former editor of <i>Hypatia: A Journal of Feminist Philosophy</i> (she resigned in 2017 due to the role that she played in the <i>Hypatia</i> transracialism controversy). Her research focuses on social and political philosophy and feminist theory. Her early work involves issues of violence against women, oppression and peacemaking, and then progresses to ethics of advocacy and violence against women in conflict settings, including war rape and just war theory. Her recent research involves these issues in addition to solidarity. She has published four single-author books and edited three academic journals, among many other publications.</p>',
